title: Stock market futures cut gains after Trump whistleblower complaint is released
text: U.S. stock index futures were slightly higher Thursday, boost by optimism around trade talks with China.

title: Oil prices hold steady as Trump touts sooner-than-expected trade deal
text: Brent crude futures were at $62.36 a barrel, down 3 cents, or 0.05%, from the previous close, by 0555 GMT.

title: Asian markets mostly rise on trade optimism
text: Asian markets mostly rose Thursday, after President Donald Trump signed one trade deal and raised optimism about another.
